<center><h2><font face="arial">How Healthy Brain influence our Intelligence</font></h2></center><br /><font face="arial"> <p>Before reading this blog many people will make their mindset as Who cares about brain health? that is why&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/can-you-die-from-a-stroke#types-of-stroke" target="_blank">The CDC[Trusted Source] </a>estimates that<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stroke" target="_blank"> strokes</a> kill about 140,000 Americans each year, and according to &nbsp <a href="https://www.world-stroke.org/world-stroke-day-campaign/why-stroke-matters/learn-about-stroke#:~:text=Stroke%20has%20already%20reached%20epidemic,will%20die%20as%20a%20result." target="_blank">World Stroke Organization</a>&nbsp Over 13 million people will have a stroke each year and around 5.5 million people will die as a result.</p><p><font color="#800080"><b>Why people don't raise questions that why these people are dying of stroke?</b></font></p>However, the human brain is known as the most complex part of the Human body. There is a high percentage of folk are claiming that Our brain is complex because of its multifunctional activity, diverse foundation, and controls over immediate reactions. But the truth is the Brain is the most beautiful and most active part of our body. In this blog, we will know how can we keep our mind sound and productive.</font>
<p></p><center><br /><a href="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-4UGgwBFTRcejUQVRabRSUXAgaRhfsQAaF92i2TC5C8hKVPS7AxZwqQn9WZWMKNtsu6Ab6Yc6vWl7IWEXQFKW4H8wESKVFbd6F083h-2DSXsRo1iSLS_b_VwaXaeeeJlBW-I3zGW1A=w2400?source=screenshot.guru"> <img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-4UGgwBFTRcejUQVRabRSUXAgaRhfsQAaF92i2TC5C8hKVPS7AxZwqQn9WZWMKNtsu6Ab6Yc6vWl7IWEXQFKW4H8wESKVFbd6F083h-2DSXsRo1iSLS_b_VwaXaeeeJlBW-I3zGW1A=w600-h315-p-k" height="300" width="475"/> </a></center><p></p>
<font face="arial">In a day's work, Human Brain has to do more jobs than a computer. So, it also needs some rest to restore its energy like a computer battery.
<p><font size="5">&nbsp 1. Take proper Sleep.</font></p><p>Based on some scientific research most experts recommend the below chart:-</p><p></p><br /><center></center><table align="center" border="1"><tbody><tr><th><p>Sleep guidelines by age</p></th></tr><tr><td><br /><ul>
<li>Birth to 3 months: 14 to 17 hours</li>
<li>4 to 11 months: 12 to 16 hours</li>
<li>1 to 2 years: 11 to 14 hours</li>
<li>3 to 5 years: 10 to 13 hours</li>
<li>6 to 12 years: 9 to 12 hours</li>
<li>13 to 18 years: 8 to 10 hours</li>
<li>18 to 64 years: 7 to 9 hours</li>
<li>65 years and older: 7 to 8 hours</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p></p><p></p>if want to learn more about sleep <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/sleep/sleep-calculator" target="_blank">Click  here</a>
<p><font size="5">&nbsp 2. Spend some time for exercise.</font></p><p>Taking a few moment for exercise will help to reduce stress hormones in our body. These days, especially since 2020, after starting The pandemic people forget to take a few moments for body stretch. Though, during lockdowns, people had spent a lot of time with their family members and learned some indoor exercises. Stroke, heart attack, and other stress-related diseases become epidemic in some regions.</p><p> if we could not able to manage time for physical activity, we can take other ways as a warmup session, like one can use stairs instead of using elevator, go for shopping on foot, doing some Voluntary work in weekends is also give a positive impact on our mind and help to believe in self and create sympathy for everyone.</p><p>go to this link to know more about &nbsp;<a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/physical-activity" target="_blank">Physical activity</a>&nbsp at different ages.</p>
<p><font size="5">&nbsp 3. A Research on How Healthy brain manage our Intelligence.</font></p><p> Here is an Article on a research based on the connection between Healthy Brain and Cognitive Skills was Conducted in 2017 September 15th by:-</p><p></p><ol> <li>Brain Center Rudolf Magnus, Department of Psychiatry, University Medical Center Utrecht, Utrecht, Netherlands.</li>
<li>Department of Radiology, University Medical Center Utrecht, Utrecht, Netherlands.</li></ol>This is the link of the ARTICLE  <a href=" https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fpsyt.2017.00154/full" target="_blank">Intelligence and Brain Efficiency: Investigating the Association between Working Memory Performance, Glutamate, and GABA.</a>
<p><font size="5">&nbsp 4. Give some Time for Yourself.</font></p><p>Some people might find relaxation during reading a book. One can enjoy their free time by reading <i><b>Hyperfocus, Hope, Can't Hurt ME, Power, Mindset,</b></i> and many more satisfactory books or if one wants some enjoyment they can watch a movie or reality show on youtube. I suggest <big><b>Steve Harvey: Family Feud show</b></big>, it is one of the best show on youtube as a comedy show. I give one of his video below:-</p>
